    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ethiopian single-string bowed spike fiddles, having a tuning-peg, bridge, and parchment-covered diamond-shaped soundbox.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000030041/Sadie, New Grove Dictionary of Musical Instruments (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Vielles etíopes de arco, de una sola cuerda, que tienen una clavija de afinación, un puente y una caja de resonancia cubierta de pergamino y en forma de diamante</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Spiesvedels met 1 snaar, stemschroef, kam, ruitvormige, met perkament bedekte klankkast; bespeeld met een strijkstok; Ethiopië.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
